{"ts": "2026-06-09T21:58:12.095985+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Unfortunately, the personal access token doesn't have write permissions to the repository, so I'm unable to push changes directly. Let me summarize my findings and proposed changes.\n\n---\n\n## Issue #6 Analysis: \"Update the safe scan profile\"\n\n### Current State\n\n**`scan_profiles/safe_local.yml`** (current):\n```yaml\nname: safe-local\nscope: localhost-only\noptions:\n  - -sV\n  - --top-ports\n  - \"100\"\nforbidden:\n  - public_ip_ranges\n  - aggressive_external_scans\n```\n\n**`scripts/run_safe_scan.sh`** (current):\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\nTARGET=${1:-127.0.0.1}\ncase \"$TARGET\" in\n  127.0.0.1|localhost) ;;\n  *) echo \"Refusing to scan non-local target: $TARGET\" >&2; exit 2 ;;\nesac\nnmap -sV --top-ports 100 -oX reports/local_scan.xml \"$TARGET\"\n```\n\n### Key Observation\n\nBoth files already include `-sV` (nmap's service/version detection flag). The issue requests \"include service/version detection\" — to make this an explicit, self-documenting configuration property in the profile YAML (rather than only relying on buried flags), the change should add a top-level `service_version_detection: true` field to `scan_profiles/safe_local.yml`.\n\n### Proposed Changes\n\n**`scan_profiles/safe_local.yml`** — add explicit `service_version_detection` field:\n```yaml\nname: safe-local\nscope: localhost-only\nservice_version_detection: true\noptions:\n  - -sV\n  - --top-ports\n  - \"100\"\nforbidden:\n  - public_ip_ranges\n  - aggressive_external_scans\n```\n\n**`scripts/run_safe_scan.sh`** — no changes needed (already includes `-sV` and the localhost guard).\n\n### Validation\n\nThe `scripts/validate_repo.py` script checks:\n1. Required files exist ✓ (no files added/removed)\n2. `run_safe_scan.sh` contains the \"Refusing to scan non-local target\" guard ✓ (script unchanged)\n\nBoth validations would continue to pass.\n\n###